<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-03-21</DATELINE><TITLE>Controlling hospital MRSA</TITLE><BODY>Recent evidence from publications describing the success of interventions to control hospital meticillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA), often in the endemic setting, is reviewed. Overall, there is cautious ground for optimism that MRSA can be controlled in a cost-effective manner by employing a bundle approach, the mainstay of which is widespread admission screening to inform patient-specific control measures.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>